    <traitlist name="Locations" abc="yes" atomic="yes" display="5"/>
    <notes>
      <![CDATA[Anarch Rep- Champion, Committed, Hard-Core

2.3 Equipment:
"Mundane" Equipment: 

BBOD Mark II

Modular pieces connect to bracer and lock into place by screw mounts. Each bracer can hold two (2) Modules: Upper and Lower.  Pressure switch on bracer triggers between Upper and Lower Module Control. 

Bracer:  Made of steel.  12 inches in length.  Bracer width of band is 1 inch.  Inside of Bracer is covered with plastic (foam filled) padding which recognizes pressure for trigger effects.    
BBOD: Negative Traits: Clumsy (In addition to other negative traits from below)

Outer Edge of BBOD: Serrated Bayonet (8 inches).  Bonus Traits: 2.  Negative Trait: Short.  Does one level of lethal damage.  Mounted on Spring mounted slide.  Can slide out 6 inches  

Module One: Shotgun
(Semi-Automatic Single Barrel  Shotgun.  Sawed off Stock, Sawed off Barrel, Forearm mount
[Attached to upper bracer].  Hand mechanism trigger [close hand in fist to release
Safety, pull fist down to shoot, raise fist up to load next shell] 
7 shot clip.  +3 traits, Neg. traits = Loud and Clumsy.  2 Dam inside of 10 feet.  2 Targets beyond 10 feet.

Module Two: Stake thrower
(Mounted on Lower Module)

. +2 traits, Neg. = Clumsy.

Double Barrel Stake thrower.  Special Ability: Staking. Hand mechanism trigger [close hand in fist to release safety, pull fist up to shoot first stake, pull fist up again to shoot second stake] On a successful hit, able to stake target on two consecutive (win or tie) Simple tests. 

Range: 30 feet. Spring loaded.  Requires 8 Physical Traits or Prowess to reload.

Module Three: Chemical Sprayer

Traits: +2, Negative: Clumsy

Game Mechanics: Sprays a 10-15 foot long, 3-5 foot wide (at base) cone of chemical agent for one turn, covering all targets in the path.  "Fuel" Canisters are mounted into place and are screwed into position (similar to air gun)

Sprayer attachment alongside of the tank, nozzle is extendable (by spring release) to 6 inches past fist. 
When retracted, same length as the canister.  Electronic igniter wired along side extended portion of nozzle.  
Hand mechanism trigger [close hand in fist to release/activate safety, pull fist down to extend nozzle, pull hand down again to activate spray/ignition] Must manually push the nozzle back into place once finished.

Description: 
Canisters: 
(10 Fl. OZ. Pressurized to 50 lbs. Pressure). Look like big CO2 tubes from a CO2 pellet gun.  8 inches long, 1 inch diameter) Composed of steel with kevlar mesh over tube.  Refillable in a Metal Shop.   Requires two turns to reload (one to remove old canister, one turn to load new canister)

Flame-thrower
Game Mechanics: Any player sprayed suffers one level of fire (aggravated) damage and must spend one turn rolling around putting out the fire or take an additional level of damage each turn.

Flame-thrower Canisters 
Isopropyl Alcohol /gasoline/oil mix (10 Fl. OZ. Pressurized to 50 lbs. Pressure). Look like big CO2 tubes from a CO2 pellet gun.  8 inches long, 1 inch diameter) Composed of steel with kevlar mesh over tube.  Refillable in a Metal Shop.   Requires two turns to reload (one to remove old canister, one turn to load new canister)

Flame-thrower attachment for BBOD: 
http://www.totse.com/files/FA031/ultfthrw.htm (Compressed fuel idea)

Module Four: Harpoon/Grappling Gun
 (Mounted on Upper Module)
Harpoon gun. +2 traits, Neg. = Clumsy.  

Single Harpoon launcher attached to reel of mountaineering line (50 foot line (300 lb. Test) on reel attached to module, can be separately attached to different cable for added length on separate reel (not on module))

Steel Grappling Hook

Range: 400 feet. Compressed Air Operated.  Uses Canister of Compressed Air. Look like big CO2 tubes from a CO2 pellet gun.  8 inches long, 1 inch diameter) Composed of steel with kevlar mesh over tube.  Refillable in a Metal Shop.   Requires two turns to reload (one to remove old canister, one turn to load new canister)

Module Five: Paint Gun Attachment
 (Mounted on Upper Module)
+2 traits, Neg. = Clumsy.  

Standard paint Air Gun.  Has 8-pellet clip running alongside the barrel.  

Range: 30 feet. Compressed Air Operated.  Uses Canister of Compressed Air. Look like big CO2 tubes from a CO2 pellet gun.  8 inches long, 1 inch diameter) Composed of steel with kevlar mesh over tube.  Refillable in a Metal Shop.   Requires two turns to reload (one to remove old canister, one turn to load new canister)

Ammo Canisters: 8 pellets.

Standard Paint Pellets (Red paint)

Module Six: Injector
(Mounted on Lower Module)
Double Barrel Injector. +2 traits, Neg. = Clumsy.  

Hand mechanism trigger [close hand in fist to release safety, pull fist up to shoot first stake, pull fist up again to shoot second injector]

Special Ability: Injection. On a successful hit, able to inject target on single (win or tie) Simple test. 

Range: 30 feet. Spring loaded.  Requires 8 Physical Traits or Prowess to reload

Injector Spikes: Hollow metal spikes (8 inches long, 1-inch diameter).  Top is unscrewed to allow insertion of chemical agent capsule (plastic capsule 3 inches long ľ inch diameter).  On impact, triggers spring which pushes forward puncturing the capsule and injecting the agent through small vents in the tip.   

Chemical Agents: 

Weakblooded Agent

Game Effects: 

Upon injection/ingestion of the dose, the character gains the Flaw: Thin Blooded for One Hour.  (All costs for Blood Traits are doubled, and may require character to spend multiple turns when powering disciplines or healing.  You cannot create a Blood Bond, and Embrace someone only if you Win (not tie) a Simple Test).  If injected into a mortal, all bashing damage is considered lethal for the duration of effect (mortal is now hemophilic)
 
Reference: http://www.dupontpharma.com/coumadin/cumadnpi.htm#pharmacology




Transmitter: 
Modified Child Alert Jr (http://www.dhq.com/metro) with GPS Beacon..  Range: 2 Miles for warning Alert.    Linked to Receiver Unit.  Can be disabled through control device (beeper).

Control Device: 
Looks like beeper.  Once active, a single button push activates "Panic Button", reacts as if puncture was detected.  Three pushes deactivates the vest.  Three more pushes reactivates vest. 

Receiver Unit:  
Must be located within 2 miles of vest. (Justin's Car's trunk) Size of an old Comaq portable (3'x2'x1', weight: 50 lbs).  Includes handheld GPS Tracking system, recording device for sound and receiver for sound signal, and signal booster.  Transmits to Main Receiver Unit located within the Cumpania.]]>
    </notes>
  </vampire>
