  <item name="Culpa-Tech Flogger" type="Equipment" subtype="Weapon" level="0" bonus="0" amount="0" lastmodified="12/17/2008 11:46:16 PM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="entangle"/>
      <trait name="shocking"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Special ability: entangle A user with melee of 2 or greater may
attempt to use the flogger to entangle. This must be called as the attack, and upon a successful physical challenge, the user must win or tie two of three chops, retested with melee. A successful challenge
entangles the limb, causing one lethal, and leaving the victim at -2
traits to use that limb, and receiving an additional lethal every action of the user due to the blades digging deeper. The victim must win a challenge to be out of the entaglement, by the same rules as grappling.
Special effect, shocking. The handle contains a stun gun like
device. If used during a normal attack, this will cause an additional
lethal of damage, considered a separate source. In addition, the
target will be at -2 traits their next attack. If used during an
entangle, it will inflict one lethal a round, and will prevent the
victim from acting unless they win a static physical against 12
traits. Winning this challenge allows them to act the remainder of the round, in case of celerity. The weapon has enough energy for 5
rounds, after which two actions must be spent changing the battery
pack. It includes a setting to cause light tingling, for sensation
only. At this setting, it lasts for one hour or scene (all pun intended).]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[A cat of nine tails, each tail made of half inch ball chain, 2 and a
half feet long, each ball with small steel curved spikes welded upon
it. The terminal ball is instead covered with an cross shaped blade over the whole end. The balls are plated in copper, with silver and gold accents in a design that emulates electricity or lightning. .
When waved in motion the entire flogger seems like a living gold and silver bolt of electricity. This plating effect is done at crafts 5,
meaning when moved properly, it effects Toreador.]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
