  <item name="Mahakala Blade" type="Equipment" subtype="Weapon" level="0" bonus="2" damage="Aggravated" amount="1" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="9/26/2003 1:00:29 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Short"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Sarrath's Claw]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[12 inch dagger engraved with the symbol of Sarrath (three curved claws tipped in blood) and empowered through the force of the drabarne's will becomes a weapon capable of doing great harm (aggravated damage) to all "magical" beings, including vampires, spirit-dwellers (spirit and Wraiths), faeries and all types of werecreatures .]]>
    </appearance>
    <notes>
      <![CDATA[In addition to the immediate damage, the weapon has a chance of inflicting additional wound levels in the five succeeding rounds as small pieces of the claw work their way deeper into the target's body. In each of the five rounds after the claw first hits a creature, the target must make a successful Physical Challenge (plus  an additional trait for each level of Fortitude for vampires) (difficulty of the wielder's Willpower) or take an additional level of lethal damage.  The magic of Sarrath's Claw on a victim is not cumulative. Further attacks from the claw will do immediate damage to an already affected victim, but not any more additional damage. However, once the effects of the first attack are over (five rounds), a new success with the claw will start the process anew.]]>
    </notes>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Acid" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" damage="Aggravated" amount="1" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="3/19/2003 1:43:12 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Concentrated formula of Hydrofluoric acid.  Acid grenades cause one level of aggravated damage to their target. What's more, unless scraped/washed off with a Static Physical Challenge (six-Trait difficulty to simulate scraping/scrubbing the acid off), the acid continues to inflict one level of aggravated damage for an additional turn  Each level of damage caused by the acid also causes the target to gain the negative Social Trait: Repugnant until healed.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter silver sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Explosive" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="10" bonus="1" damage="Lethal" amount="2" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="1/12/2008 8:36:36 PM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2">
      <trait name="Blood"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[- These grenades deliver damage through explosive force. This grenade has an effective radius of up to one step around the target, and it inflicts two levels of lethal damage.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter red sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Flash Bangs" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" amount="0" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="3/19/2003 12:14:09 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[These devices emit a blinding flash of light and a deafening (135 decibel) blast of sound simultaneously, leaving targets dazed and vulnerable. They do no damage, but all unaware characters in the area (10' x 10' x 10') must make a Static Physical Challenge against six Traits or be considered blind and deaf for the next four turns. They are then two Traits down on all Physical Challenges for the rest of the scene after that. Characters unfortunate enough to be using Heightened Senses or similar powers at the time of the explosion fail the challenge automatically and remain blind and deaf for the rest of the scene. They are also two Traits down on all Physical Challenges for the remainder of the session.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter white sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Incendiary" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" damage="Aggravated" amount="1" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="3/19/2003 12:10:40 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Incendiary"/>
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Thermite grenades cause one level of aggravated damage to their target. Unless extinguished with a Static Physical Challenge (six-Trait difficulty to simulate rolling around or beat out the flames), the Thermite continue to inflict one level of aggravated damage for 3 turns (approximately 12 seconds).   Flammable material ignited by the Thermite will burn for five minutes or until put out.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter  orange sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - KnockOut" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" amount="0" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="3/19/2003 1:40:26 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[fill roughly a large room-sized area (10' x 10' x 10') with a gas derived from VERSED syrup. All breathing targets in the area must make a Static Physical Challenge against 12 Traits or fall unconscious for two hours and lose their memories for the five minutes before they inhaled the gas. The cloud dissipates in 5 minutes indoors and 2 minutes outdoors, and all targets must make tests each turn until they are out of the area of effect.   Note: this gas does not normally effect Kindred as they do not need to breath.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter purple sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Regurgitative" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" amount="0" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="3/19/2003 1:41:27 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Must make Simple Test to avoid being nauseated for one scene; no spending Willpower to avoid the test.  If nauseated, must spend next turn choking, retching and gagging (losing all actions that turn).  (For Kindred: When nauseated, make a Simple test to determine how much Blood has been vomited up: Win: 1 Trait, Tie: 2 Traits, Lose: 3 Traits.)    The victim is One Trait down on all Physical Challenges for the rest of the scene/15 minutes. Characters unfortunate enough to be using Heightened Senses: Smell or have Acute Sense: Smell active at the time of the explosion fail the challenge automatically and remain nauseated for the rest of the scene. They are also one Trait down on all Physical Challenges for the remainder of the hour.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter green sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Rotter" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" damage="Aggravated" amount="1" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="1/25/2004 7:19:05 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[75%/25% Concentrated formula of hydrofluoric acid and acetone. A successful hit causes one level of aggravated damage to the target. As the acid quickly permeates the skin and begins necrosis of the tissue and bone structure, the actetone begins defatting the skin tissue, causing the target to gain the negative Physical Trait: Clumsy or Lame as the tissue, muscle and bone of the affected limb is destroyed. By making two successful Simple Tests (win only) after a successful hit, the target's head is struck. Doing so kill mortals instantly and causes Kindred to gain the negative Mental Traits: Oblivious and Witless in addition to rendering them unable to use the powers of Celerity, Fortitude and Potence.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1 " diameter gold sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Smoke" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" amount="1" lastmodified="3/19/2003 12:08:46 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Concealment"/>
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[These grenades fill roughly a large room-sized area (10' x 10' x 10') with thick black smoke.  Treat those within the cloud as blind for purposes of Trait penalties (two Traits down in resolution of challenges and are forced to make a single retest on any successful challenge), and any characters shooting into/ through it are at a one-Trait penalty.  The cloud dissipates in 5 minutes indoors and 2 minutes outdoors.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter  black sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Steel Foam" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="0" damage="Armor Levels" amount="10" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="3/19/2003 12:12:21 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[These grenades cover targets with a viscous, sticky substance that hardens quickly into something nearly as strong as their namesake. Characters struck by this substance must make a Static Physical Challenge against 14 Traits in order to make any movement of consequence. The foam effectively has 10 health levels that must be removed before the target is freed. The only other way to escape is to use the correct chemical solution (provided separately with the grenade).]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter blue sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade - Tear Gas" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" amount="0" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="3/19/2003 12:09:30 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[These grenades fill a large room (10' x 10' x 10') with caustic, irritating gas. Characters exposed to this gas must make a Static Physical Challenge against 10 Traits or be rendered incapacitated by intense discomfort and labored breathing. Those who resist are still at a two-Trait penalty on all actions for the rest of the scene due to their extreme distraction and impairment, unless they are protected or otherwise immune to the gas's effects somehow.  Vampires need not make the Static Challenge, but they still suffer penalties on all tests related to vision (their eyes can be affected). The cloud dissipates in 5 minutes indoors and 2 minutes outdoors.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter yellow sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
  <item name="Marble Grenade-  Concussion" type="Equipment" subtype="Ranged Weapon" level="0" bonus="1" damage="Bashing" amount="2" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="3/19/2003 12:15:40 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Spray"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Tiny"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[These grenades deliver damage through pure kinetic force, making it unlikely that the target will suffer lasting injury. This grenade has an effective radius of up to one step around the target, and it inflicts two levels of  bashing damage on a successful attack. This damage (even more temporary than normal bashing damage) fades at the end of the scene/hour, whichever is longer.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1"diameter grey  sphere]]>
    </appearance>
  </item>
