  <item name="PEA (Protective External Armor) Coat" type="Equipment" subtype="Armor" level="0" bonus="0" damage="Armor Levels" amount="3" lastmodified="1/25/2004 9:03:32 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Fire-Retardant"/>
      <trait name="Taser Retardant"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Taser Retardant: 
The material does not conduct electrical charge. Attacks that would normally cause the subject to be stunned or incapacitated through electrical damage are ignored.
 
Fire Retardant: 
The material does not catch on fire. Attacks that would normally cause the subject to burn over successive turns can still cause initial damage (from heat and initial flame), but the fire goes out automatically. Wearing Fire Retardant material grants the wearer a +1 bonus on Courage tests against Fire (Rotschreck)]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[Coat designed to look like standard Navy Pea Coat]]>
    </appearance>
    <notes>
      <![CDATA[Made from Triple weave Nomex/Kevlar fire resistant material with braided strips of Nomex woven into the lining that grounds any oncoming electrical charge
 out instead of allowing it to transfer to the body (note: this only covers the body, the head, hands
 and legs are still susceptible) Polymer reinforced plates are also inserted into the front and back of
 the jacket providing additional protection to the torso area.]]>
    </notes>
  </item>
  <item name="Pendant of Hidden Diablerie" type="Talisman" subtype="Enhancement" level="0" bonus="0" amount="0" conceal="Pocket" lastmodified="1/25/2004 7:20:25 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[While worn, any Aura Perception on the wearer will NOT show diablerie veins in their aura.  As the aura is static, it will also not show any lies the wearer states. 

(For purpose of seeing through enchantment: 21 Social Traits, Performance: Illusioncasting x 5, and Subterfuge)]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[Small steel pendant in shape of a phoenix attached to a simple metal necklace.]]>
    </appearance>
    <notes>
      <![CDATA[Created by the Ravnos Justin Case using Horrid Reality, Perminancy, as well as Illusioncasting x5 and Crafts- Metalworking x2]]>
    </notes>
  </item>
  <item name="Personal Protection System" type="Equipment" subtype="Armor" level="0" bonus="0" amount="0" conceal="Jacket" lastmodified="1/25/2004 6:56:56 AM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique" note="Justin Case"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Game Effect: Acts as GPS Tracking system for the wearer.If the mesh is pierced, the following occurs: 
1.  Transmits signal to Receiver Unit. 
2. Warning message is transmitted to 3 predetermined numbers. (determined by player)
2.  Microphone woven into the upper right shoulder activates and records all sound within 15 foot radius for 20 minutes.  This is recorded to both a recording unit in the vest and sent to the receiver unit.   Transmit is always on, but not recording unless activated by puncture or command from receiver.  Transmitter in vest: Range: 3 Miles. Linked to Receiver Unit. Can be operated through control device.]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[:  Lightweight cloth vest with wire mesh (1/16th inch gap between wires) woven between the layers of cloth.  Can be worn concealed  under other clothing.   Transmitter is wired into the lower back of the vest.]]>
    </appearance>
    <notes>
      <![CDATA[Control Device: Looks like beeper.  While active, a single button push activates "Panic Button", reacts as if puncture was detected.  Two pushes activates recording within Receiver Unit without puncture alert. Receiver Unit:  Size: Length: 3' Width: 2' Depth: 1'Weight: 50 poundsMust be located within 2 miles of vest. Includes handheld GPS Tracking system, recording device for sound (maximum eight hours) and receiver for sound signal, and signal booster.  Transmits automatically via cell modem to Main Receiver Unit (located within security offices of Club Patshiva in Phoneix AZ) with Receiver Unit GPS location once per hour and alerts Main Receiver Unit immediately if Panic or puncture are activated.]]>
    </notes>
  </item>
